  sodium: 630 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/vegan-sweet-potato-coconut-curry-noodles-66955e50b0a47382be8702f4
servings: 2
---

Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Roughly chop @peanuts{1/2%ounce}. Dice @sweet potato{1}(diced into 1/2-inch pieces)
into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary and cut into
11⁄2-inch pieces. Quarter @lime{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Once water is boiling, add @lo mein noodles{4.5%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Drain noodles and rinse under cold water for ~{30%seconds}.

While noodles cook, heat a #large dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add peanuts
and cook, stirring frequently, until golden brown and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.
Transfer to a #plate.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in pan used for peanuts over medium-high
heat. Add sweet potato and a pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until browned and slightly tender, ~{7%minutes}. (Lower heat if sweet potato
starts to brown too quickly.)

While sweet potato cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @coconut milk{1},
@sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, half the
@curry powder{1%tbsp}, and 1/2 cup water (all the curry powder and 1 cup water
for 4 servings).

Stir green beans and sauce mixture into pan with sweet potato. Bring to a boil,
then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until veggies are tender,
~{6-8%minutes}. (If sauce seems too thick, add a splash of water.) Remove from
heat.

Add drained noodles and juice from half the lime to pan with veggies and sauce;
toss to coat. Season with salt.

Divide coconut curry noodles between #bowls{} and top with peanuts and cilantro.
Squeeze remaining lime wedges over the top and serve.